Excel.' No cost-of-error, FTE burden, or projected savings has ever been put to a number, which is exactly why the internal business case has stalled. Quantifying the manual-process cost is a required move."}, "champion": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Avoma calls 6 May / 5 Jun / 25 Jun 2025, Carlos Dolz Bautista", "Next_Step__c 29 Apr 2026", "SF LastActivityDate 2026-06-15"], "narrative": "Carlos Dolz Bautista (Sourcing Associate) is a developing champion, not a power champion. He drove all three 2025 calls, articulated the pain and requirements in detail, praised the platform ('your solution is quite robust... it's a good solution', 25 Jun 2025), and personally re-opened the deal after the freeze ('we would like to revisit this conversation in mid-2026', 29 Apr 2026). But he has no budget authority, has never introduced a decision-maker, legal, IT, or finance despite Zycus's requests, and deflected on widening the room ('by the moment it's only us'). What has developed: sustained engagement and genuine advocacy for solving the problem. What is missing: internal selling power and access to whoever funds the ~EUR 20M budget. He is at risk of going quiet, having not replied to the 15 Jun 2026 re-contact."}, "competition": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Avoma call 6 May 2025, Carlos Dolz Bautista", "Avoma call 5 Jun 2025, Carlos Dolz Bautista", "Avoma call 25 Jun 2025, Carlos Dolz Bautista"], "narrative": "The real competitor is the do-nothing / stay-on-Excel status quo, sustained by budget uncertainty and organizational inertia rather than a rival vendor. Oracle ERP is the incumbent for finance and POs and stays in place; Carlos called it 'a closed system... we see limitations in the flexibility we need' (6 May 2025), which is the wedge for Zycus as the flexible upstream procurement layer that integrates with Oracle downstream. Coupa was evaluated ~2020-2021 during the Oracle selection and was not chosen ('we were analyzing Coupa and all different models'), and has not resurfaced. Zycus met every functional requirement in the demos, so we win on fit; we lose to inertia unless we quantify ROI and reach a funder."}, "identify_pain": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Avoma call 5 Jun 2025, Carlos Dolz Bautista", "Avoma call 25 Jun 2025, Carlos Dolz Bautista"], "narrative": "The operational pain is well established and owner-attributed. Carlos (Sourcing Associate, the pain owner) described a fully manual, Excel-based process for ~600 suppliers: 'everything is handmade, it's very manual... we spend a lot of time trying to control, and we miss information because you can lose email' (5 Jun 2025). Certificate/document renewals across regulated medical suppliers are tracked by hand and risk lapsing, and invoices are 'controlled manually' wasting team time (25 Jun 2025). The pain is real and recurring, but it is felt at the operational level by a 3-person team, not yet framed as a financial or compliance risk that a budget owner would fund."}, "paper_process": {"status": "gap", "sources": ["Avoma call 25 Jun 2025, Carlos Dolz Bautista and Pierre Meraud"], "narrative": "Contracting mechanics are essentially unknown. The only concrete signals are that Teladoc uses DocuSign ('we are working with DocuSign', 25 Jun 2025) and that Zycus requires a minimum 4-to-5-year term, which Carlos resisted in favor of annual renewals. Pierre floated a trial-then-commit structure with an exit clause ('a trial period... then a 4 or 5 years contract... I can negotiate internally an exit clause', 25 Jun 2025) but nothing was formalized. Legal, procurement, InfoSec, and MSA/SOW steps have never been mapped. Visibility would come from securing a written phased-commercial proposal and asking Carlos who owns contract sign-off and vendor security review."}, "economic_buyer": {"status": "gap", "sources": ["Avoma call 5 Jun 2025, Carlos Dolz Bautista", "Avoma call 6 May 2025, Carlos Dolz Bautista", "Avoma call 25 Jun 2025, Carlos Dolz Bautista"], "narrative": "No economic buyer has been identified after 13 months. Carlos confirmed on 5 Jun 2025 'it's only between Natasha, Vincent and me... 3 people' and on 6 May 2025 that New York HQ 'don't know' the detail and would only be looped in for reporting: 'the key decisions... will be in our side'. So budget authority sits somewhere above this 3-person sourcing team but has never been named or engaged, and the cost question Carlos flagged ('how long to develop and the cost are the two important questions', 25 Jun 2025) has no owner. Naming and reaching whoever signs the ~EUR 20M procurement budget in the Barcelona international unit is the single highest-value MEDDPICC move."}, "decision_process": {"status": "partial", "sources": ["Avoma call 6 May 2025, Carlos Dolz Bautista", "Next_Step__c (29 Apr 2026, 23 Jun 2025)"], "narrative": "The buyer is running an informal, self-directed benchmark, not a structured RFP. Carlos described it on 6 May 2025 as 'just starting to check the market benchmarking... it's more like by ourselves', with the international Barcelona unit deciding independently and HQ merely informed. The intended path (shortlist July 2025, decision September 2025, implementation early 2026) collapsed into an 8-month freeze and a stated 'revisit mid-2026'. The approval chain above the 3-person team is undefined. There is no mutual close plan, no confirmed procurement/legal gate, and the buyer's cadence is now driven entirely by their internal analysis rather than any external event."}, "decision_criteria": {"status": "confirmed", "sources": ["Avoma call 25 Jun 2025, Carlos Dolz Bautista", "Avoma call 5 Jun 2025, Carlos Dolz Bautista"], "narrative": "The evaluation criteria are clear from the discovery and demo calls: supplier onboarding and registration with enforced document/certificate control, a contract repository with expiry alerts and clause-completeness checks, flexible roles/permissions across heterogeneous business units, integration with Oracle for